description: Back-formation from nutation (1610s), from Latin nūtātiō (“nodding”), from nūtō (“I nod”), from Proto-Indo-European *neu-. Compare mutate.

verbs.description: nutate (third-person singular simple present nutates, present participle nutating, simple past and past participle nutated)

entries.meaning: (intransitive, engineering) To wobble; to make a circular rocking motion.
